MasterLute - a World of Warcraft (1.12.1) AddOn
===================================================

Installation:

Put "MasterLute" folder into ".../World of Warcraft/Interface/AddOns/".
Create AddOns folder if necessary

After Installation directory tree should look like the following

'''
World of Warcraft
  `- Interface
     `- AddOns
        `- MasterLute
           |- README.txt
           |- MasterLute.lua
           |- MasterLute.toc
'''

Features:
- Sends raid chat message with some predefined variables by user

Usage:
- Shift click on the loot item, set price if neccessary and hit "Send" to 
  post the message
  
Commands:
	/masterlute enable (enables addon)
	/masterlute disable (disables addon)
	/masterlute autoload (enables or disables autoload in current zone)
	/masterlute price set <itemLink | itemID> <number> (sets the default price for item)
	/masterlute price get <itemLink | itemID> (returns item price, if any)
	/masterlute price list [, page] (lists items and prices)

Requested by:
